1
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,833
[melancholy Mandopop music playing]

2
00:00:15,541 --> 00:00:18,875
[Yu-chieh singing in Mandarin]

3
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:38,875
[in English] ♪ <i>What's lost is lost </i>♪

4
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:43,375
- [objects crashing, muffled]
- [music fades]

5
00:00:43,458 --> 00:00:45,291
CONTEST NEXT WEEK,
YU-CHIEH, ARE YOU GOING?

6
00:00:45,375 --> 00:00:46,625
THIS SONG SEEMS A BIT SAD

7
00:00:46,708 --> 00:00:48,875
- [Chia-jen] Yu-chieh!
- [doorknob clicks]

8
00:00:48,958 --> 00:00:51,291
[crashing continues]

9
00:00:51,375 --> 00:00:52,458
[Chia-jen] Yu-chieh!

10
00:00:54,125 --> 00:00:55,833
- [Yu-chieh sighs]
- Are you in there?

11
00:00:56,458 --> 00:00:58,458
- [door banging]
- [doorknob rattling]

12
00:00:58,541 --> 00:01:00,166
[Chia-jen] Why are you hiding
in your room?

13
00:01:00,250 --> 00:01:02,875
- [banging continues]
- Open the door, Yu-chieh!

14
00:01:02,958 --> 00:01:08,208
[music resumes]

15
00:01:08,291 --> 00:01:10,291
[Yu-chieh singing
in Mandarin on recording]

16
00:01:24,791 --> 00:01:25,791
[Yu-chieh sniffles]

17
00:01:27,166 --> 00:01:29,708
[sniffling]

18
00:01:30,916 --> 00:01:33,541
- [music continues]
- [singing continues]

19
00:01:33,625 --> 00:01:35,833
[no audible dialogue]

20
00:01:43,958 --> 00:01:46,208
You've forgotten what today is?!

21
00:01:46,291 --> 00:01:48,416
- [guitar smashing]
- What are you doing?

22
00:01:49,250 --> 00:01:54,666
[music continues]

23
00:02:00,166 --> 00:02:03,125
[music fades]

24
00:02:03,208 --> 00:02:05,708
[opening theme music playing]

25
00:02:09,583 --> 00:02:11,125
[singer singing in Mandarin]

26
00:02:33,583 --> 00:02:36,125
[music ends]

27
00:02:36,208 --> 00:02:39,666
[singing in Mandarin]

28
00:02:53,458 --> 00:02:54,791
Amazing!

29
00:02:55,583 --> 00:02:57,708
Did you write it yourself?

30
00:02:57,791 --> 00:02:58,791
[in English] Yeah.

31
00:02:59,291 --> 00:03:00,916
[roommate] Who is it about?

32
00:03:03,041 --> 00:03:06,666
Someone… I never wanna see again.

33
00:03:08,166 --> 00:03:10,416
You never want to see them again?

34
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:12,333
But you wrote a song for them?

35
00:03:13,791 --> 00:03:14,833
Is that weird?

36
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,333
No. [chuckles]

37
00:03:17,416 --> 00:03:19,166
I think I understand.

38
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:24,083
Because I also have someone
I… I'm willing… to…

39
00:03:24,166 --> 00:03:27,708
- [paper rustling]
- [roommate inhales]

40
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:31,083
…willing to…

41
00:03:33,041 --> 00:03:36,041
uh… willing to dance for. [chuckles]

42
00:03:36,125 --> 00:03:38,000
Then he must be special.

43
00:03:39,291 --> 00:03:40,291
Uh…

44
00:03:41,291 --> 00:03:43,791
Yeah! He was my first.

45
00:03:45,083 --> 00:03:47,583
My first… first love.

46
00:03:47,666 --> 00:03:48,500
[both chuckle]

47
00:03:49,208 --> 00:03:50,541
And thank you.

48
00:03:50,625 --> 00:03:52,958
Tell Kai Sheng
these two work well together.

49
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:58,333
AUDITIONS FOR "SIX BROTHERS, ONE SISTER"
PLEASE WALK STRAIGHT AHEAD

50
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:03,833
[Yu-chieh] Hey.

51
00:04:05,458 --> 00:04:08,708
- It's normal to be nervous.
- [chuckles]

52
00:04:08,791 --> 00:04:10,791
I made you look worse.

53
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:12,000
No.

54
00:04:12,083 --> 00:04:15,583
And actually, I was nervous. Sorry.

55
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:17,000
Do you audition often?

56
00:04:17,625 --> 00:04:20,000
Mm-hmm. I do.

57
00:04:20,583 --> 00:04:22,083
You wanna be an actor?

58
00:04:22,750 --> 00:04:26,625
I don't know. I'm not good
when people are watching.

59
00:04:27,583 --> 00:04:30,583
I know how you feel.
These things also make me nervous.

60
00:04:31,208 --> 00:04:33,875
You mean before an audition?

61
00:04:33,958 --> 00:04:35,458
Yeah. Oh.

62
00:04:37,166 --> 00:04:39,125
I'm playing at this.

63
00:04:41,416 --> 00:04:42,750
- [roommate] Next week.
- Yeah.

64
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:44,958
I've been trying
to get in for three years.

65
00:04:45,541 --> 00:04:47,791
And I finally got in. See you there?

66
00:04:48,750 --> 00:04:49,750
Bye.

67
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:51,500
Bye-bye.

68
00:04:55,083 --> 00:04:58,541
<i>In that audition two years ago,</i>
<i>I met Yu-chieh for the first time.</i>

69
00:04:58,625 --> 00:05:00,250
[Yu-chieh's music track playing]

70
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:14,708
[music continues]

71
00:05:15,291 --> 00:05:18,041
[Yu-chieh singing in Mandarin]

72
00:05:30,666 --> 00:05:32,916
[roommate] <i>Yu-chieh is the type</i>
<i>who shines wherever she is.</i>

73
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:36,250
[in English] ♪ <i>What's lost is lost… </i>♪

74
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:38,833
[roommate] <i>I can't help</i>
<i>but be captivated by her.</i>

75
00:05:41,708 --> 00:05:47,125
♪ <i>hold Nothing but right now </i>♪

76
00:05:47,208 --> 00:05:48,208
[roommate] Whoo!

77
00:05:48,291 --> 00:05:50,041
[audience cheering]

78
00:05:50,125 --> 00:05:51,125
[music stops]

79
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,583
[Yu-chieh] Thank you.

80
00:05:59,166 --> 00:06:04,375
[roommate humming Yu-chieh's song]

81
00:06:07,666 --> 00:06:08,750
[Yu-chieh] Hey!

82
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,250
Hey, wait!

83
00:06:13,041 --> 00:06:14,708
Hey! Wait.

84
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:16,541
I need to thank you for coming.

85
00:06:16,625 --> 00:06:18,083
Should we get some food?

86
00:06:18,166 --> 00:06:20,333
- [roommate] Uh… [chuckles]
- Come on.

87
00:06:20,416 --> 00:06:21,750
Let's get a late-night snack.

88
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:23,458
- [roommate] Okay. Let's go.
- Hurry!

89
00:06:23,541 --> 00:06:25,083
What should we get? Any ideas?

90
00:06:25,166 --> 00:06:28,250
Whatever you like. Udon, kebab, hot pot.

91
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:29,458
<i>By the way, what's your name?</i>

92
00:06:29,541 --> 00:06:31,750
- [roommate] <i>I'm Li Ting-en.</i>
- [Yu-chieh] <i>I'm Chen Yu-chieh.</i>

93
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:35,041
- [uplifting Mandopop music playing]
- [singer singing in Mandarin]

94
00:06:35,125 --> 00:06:37,958
- HAVE YOU FOUND A PLACE TO LIVE?
- NO, IT'S HARD TO FIND A STUDIO IN TAIPEI

95
00:06:38,041 --> 00:06:40,125
- I HAVE AN IDEA, HEAR ME OUT
- SURE! I'M OKAY WITH THAT!

96
00:06:40,208 --> 00:06:42,583
- YOU KNEW WHAT I WAS GONNA SAY?
- IT'S OKAY IF YOU DON'T WANNA…

97
00:06:42,666 --> 00:06:44,250
[Ting-en] <i>We quickly became best friends.</i>

98
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:45,333
FINE, LET'S LIVE TOGETHER!

99
00:06:45,416 --> 00:06:46,791
[both straining]

100
00:06:46,875 --> 00:06:47,875
[Yu-chieh] Ah!

101
00:06:47,958 --> 00:06:49,708
[Ting-en] <i>We moved into</i>
<i>an apartment together.</i>

102
00:06:49,791 --> 00:06:51,041
[Yu-chieh] Mm-mmm.

103
00:06:51,125 --> 00:06:52,916
Ahh! [laughing]

104
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,666
[both] One, two, three!

105
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:57,541
- [music continues]
- [singing continues]

106
00:06:57,625 --> 00:07:00,000
[both] Rock, paper, scissors!
Rock, paper, scissors!

107
00:07:00,083 --> 00:07:01,458
[Yu-chieh groans]

108
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,750
[bell chiming]

109
00:07:24,916 --> 00:07:26,708
[both] Rock, paper, scissors.

110
00:07:26,791 --> 00:07:28,041
- Yeah! Whoo!
- Hey, you went late.

111
00:07:28,125 --> 00:07:29,833
- That's not fair.
- [vocalizing]

112
00:07:29,916 --> 00:07:31,166
Bye!

113
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:32,250
[Ting-en] Hey.

114
00:07:32,333 --> 00:07:35,583
- [music continues]
- [singing continues]

115
00:07:36,666 --> 00:07:38,791
[both] Whoo!

116
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:41,833
- Thank you, ladies and gentlemen.
- [Yu-chieh trills]

117
00:07:41,916 --> 00:07:43,125
Bye-bye.

118
00:07:43,208 --> 00:07:44,708
You're too much.

119
00:07:44,791 --> 00:07:46,416
Your energy is so high right now.

120
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:49,291
- Why aren't you like that in auditions?
- Hey.

121
00:07:49,375 --> 00:07:53,291
Don't talk about auditions.
I'm pretty sure I failed the last one too.

122
00:07:53,375 --> 00:07:56,833
So what? They didn't contact me either.

123
00:07:56,916 --> 00:07:59,041
Who cares?
It could just be a budget thing.

124
00:07:59,125 --> 00:08:00,541
Are you sure?

125
00:08:00,625 --> 00:08:02,583
I'm just guessing. [blows raspberry]

126
00:08:02,666 --> 00:08:03,791
[Ting-en sighs]

127
00:08:03,875 --> 00:08:07,833
Even if they have the budget,
they won't cast me. Useless.

128
00:08:08,791 --> 00:08:11,041
- Stop talking like that.
- [hand slaps]

129
00:08:11,125 --> 00:08:13,791
[Ting-en] I can't help it. It's true.

130
00:08:14,291 --> 00:08:15,541
[Yu-chieh] Fine.

131
00:08:19,083 --> 00:08:20,291
What's that?

132
00:08:20,375 --> 00:08:22,708
- You know tarot cards?
- Don't talk. Just watch.

133
00:08:25,208 --> 00:08:26,041
[chuckles]

134
00:08:27,041 --> 00:08:29,375
Pick a card.
If I guess which one you pick,

135
00:08:29,458 --> 00:08:31,750
then you have to stop
being so unconfident.

136
00:08:31,833 --> 00:08:33,250
Ugh. It's just luck.

137
00:08:33,916 --> 00:08:35,500
- Well, let's see. One.
- [box taps]

138
00:08:38,541 --> 00:08:39,583
Two?

139
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:43,166
Or three?

140
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:48,916
[chuckles] It's three.

141
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:50,875
No way! You cheated somehow.

142
00:08:50,958 --> 00:08:53,125
You looked at these two,
but you didn't look at this one.

143
00:08:53,208 --> 00:08:54,208
[Ting-en] You're kidding.

144
00:08:54,291 --> 00:08:56,083
How did you learn that? Teach me.

145
00:08:59,291 --> 00:09:00,583
From my dad.

146
00:09:00,666 --> 00:09:02,958
[sentimental music playing]

147
00:09:03,041 --> 00:09:04,041
I see.

148
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:08,708
What if I use this?

149
00:09:10,708 --> 00:09:11,958
Try to do it now.

150
00:09:13,916 --> 00:09:15,541
Can you still do it?

151
00:09:15,625 --> 00:09:17,541
Say it again with the mask.

152
00:09:17,625 --> 00:09:19,916
- [Ting-en] Say what?
- Your audition lines.

153
00:09:20,583 --> 00:09:22,458
[Ting-en] No. That's so weird.

154
00:09:22,541 --> 00:09:24,458
- Ready?
- Hey. Ah…

155
00:09:24,541 --> 00:09:25,708
And action.

156
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:32,000
Hi, I'm Li Ting-en. 18 years old.
157 centimeters. 40 kilograms.

157
00:09:32,083 --> 00:09:34,875
My interests are watching movies
and skateboarding. I usually like…

158
00:09:34,958 --> 00:09:36,833
<i>Yu-chieh wanted me to wear a mask</i>

159
00:09:36,916 --> 00:09:38,625
<i>to help me practice</i>
<i>speaking to the camera.</i>

160
00:09:38,708 --> 00:09:40,000
<i>As if that would change anything.</i>

161
00:09:40,083 --> 00:09:41,083
It looks so good.

162
00:09:41,166 --> 00:09:42,958
[Ting-en] <i>She even taught me</i>
<i>how to edit videos</i>

163
00:09:43,041 --> 00:09:44,125
<i>and reviewed things with me.</i>

164
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:45,666
Do I really have to post this online?

165
00:09:45,750 --> 00:09:48,666
Nowadays, you gotta market yourself
if you wanna be famous.

166
00:09:49,750 --> 00:09:51,708
[Ting-en sighs] Mmm…

167
00:09:51,791 --> 00:09:55,416
I can barely act. How can I be famous?

168
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:57,750
You just need some material.

169
00:09:58,333 --> 00:09:59,791
[Ting-en] Mmm…

170
00:09:59,875 --> 00:10:01,625
[paper rustling]

171
00:10:02,208 --> 00:10:03,208
[Yu-chieh] Here.

172
00:10:04,875 --> 00:10:07,750
No, I can't. I'm not good enough.

173
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:10,166
Find something interesting.

174
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:12,625
Who even still reads that?

175
00:10:12,708 --> 00:10:13,708
[Yu-chieh] Hey.

176
00:10:14,291 --> 00:10:17,333
- [Ting-en] What?
- That series actually got cancelled.

177
00:10:17,416 --> 00:10:19,333
- Really?
- Look.

178
00:10:19,958 --> 00:10:21,041
You're right.

179
00:10:21,708 --> 00:10:23,083
You're really a jinx.

180
00:10:23,166 --> 00:10:24,625
You're the jinx.

181
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,000
What?

182
00:10:28,083 --> 00:10:30,750
I got an idea. To go viral.

183
00:10:31,583 --> 00:10:32,583
Tell me.

184
00:10:34,125 --> 00:10:35,333
[Yu-chieh] Predictions.

185
00:10:35,416 --> 00:10:36,750
PANDEMIC HITS FILM AND TV INDUSTRY

186
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:37,916
[Yo Tzu] Wait.

187
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,333
Why did you upload from a café?

188
00:10:40,416 --> 00:10:42,125
[music fades]

189
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,666
'Cause Yu-chieh's dad
didn't want her to go online.

190
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:50,333
- We didn't want him to find out.
- [Chia-jen sighs]

191
00:10:51,416 --> 00:10:53,583
[Ting-en] After all, her dad's a cop.

192
00:10:55,291 --> 00:10:58,416
So, you tried to hide.

193
00:10:59,166 --> 00:11:01,250
We didn't do it on purpose.

194
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:04,833
We didn't upload much.
Only, like, once a month.

195
00:11:05,916 --> 00:11:10,000
It was just for fun at the start.
We didn't have many subscribers.

196
00:11:10,583 --> 00:11:14,375
But then last week, Yu-chieh disappeared.

197
00:11:16,125 --> 00:11:17,416
[uneasy music playing]

198
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:19,666
- [Yu-chieh] Excuse me?
- [clerk] Hello.

199
00:11:19,750 --> 00:11:22,208
- One hour.
- Sure.

200
00:11:22,291 --> 00:11:24,250
Number 18's free.

201
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:26,708
- [Yu-chieh] Okay. Thanks.
- Thank you. Come on through.

202
00:11:28,916 --> 00:11:31,916
[phone camera clicking]

203
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,875
Hey. The lighting's so good today.

204
00:11:34,458 --> 00:11:35,416
Let me get you.

205
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:36,833
- [Yu-chieh] No.
- Come on. Don't be shy.

206
00:11:36,916 --> 00:11:38,375
- You took so many yesterday.
- So cute!

207
00:11:38,458 --> 00:11:39,625
[Yu-chieh, chuckling] Go away.

208
00:11:40,208 --> 00:11:41,208
[phone chimes]

209
00:11:41,291 --> 00:11:42,375
[Ting-en] Huh?

210
00:11:42,458 --> 00:11:43,916
I got an AirDrop.

211
00:11:44,458 --> 00:11:45,791
[Yu-chieh] What? From who?

212
00:11:45,875 --> 00:11:46,875
ACCEPT

213
00:11:58,166 --> 00:11:59,916
[music continues]

214
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,000
[Yu-chieh] What is it?

215
00:12:01,625 --> 00:12:02,625
[Ting-en] Hey.

216
00:12:05,083 --> 00:12:06,083
[Yu-chieh] Show me.

217
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:08,708
Wait. Wait.

218
00:12:09,208 --> 00:12:10,333
Wait.

219
00:12:10,416 --> 00:12:11,875
Did you notice anyone?

220
00:12:22,125 --> 00:12:24,958
He even came into my room.
What's happening?

221
00:12:26,583 --> 00:12:28,125
He sent it via AirDrop.

222
00:12:28,208 --> 00:12:30,000
Doesn't that mean
he's in the house right now?

223
00:12:30,083 --> 00:12:31,250
Calm down. Calm down!

224
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:32,958
- It doesn't mean that.
- But what if he…

225
00:12:33,041 --> 00:12:35,125
- But he's close.
- Call the police.

226
00:12:35,208 --> 00:12:37,291
[music continues]

227
00:12:37,875 --> 00:12:40,083
[Ting-en] <i>Yu-chieh</i>
<i>didn't come home that night.</i>

228
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:43,125
<i>And then I received this video.</i>

229
00:12:43,208 --> 00:12:45,333
[Ting-en breathing heavily]

230
00:12:45,416 --> 00:12:48,166
<i>He used Yu-chieh's phone to send it to me.</i>

231
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:51,041
<i>We didn't have time to call the police.</i>

232
00:12:52,416 --> 00:12:54,708
USE WITCH BABA TO POST THE PREDICTIONS
ACCORDING TO THE DATE

233
00:12:54,791 --> 00:12:57,291
<i>He wanted me to make</i>
<i>four predictions on specific dates.</i>

234
00:12:57,375 --> 00:13:01,625
<i>And he said not to contact anyone,</i>
<i>or he would kill Yu-chieh.</i>

235
00:13:02,666 --> 00:13:04,625
[Ting-en sniffles, sighs]

236
00:13:05,458 --> 00:13:09,916
[Witch Baba on video] <i>In the future,</i>
<i>someone will be shot dead.</i>

237
00:13:10,708 --> 00:13:12,916
[Ting-en] <i>I filmed the first prediction,</i>

238
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,958
<i>but I didn't expect</i>
<i>Wei Yen to really get shot.</i>

239
00:13:16,041 --> 00:13:18,500
- [officer 1] <i>Get a med unit here now!</i>
- [officer 2] <i>Stop filming.</i>

240
00:13:18,583 --> 00:13:19,541
[music swells]

241
00:13:19,625 --> 00:13:21,125
[officer 1] <i>Are you okay? Were you hit?</i>

242
00:13:21,208 --> 00:13:23,958
[Ting-en breathing shakily, sniffling]

243
00:13:24,041 --> 00:13:26,291
<i>I didn't know who I could trust.</i>

244
00:13:26,375 --> 00:13:32,166
[music subsides, continues]

245
00:13:32,250 --> 00:13:35,083
[Ting-en tapping phone]

246
00:13:35,166 --> 00:13:38,500
[typing]

247
00:13:38,583 --> 00:13:39,666
WHO EXACTLY ARE YOU?

248
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:42,041
[Ting-en] <i>It was after Wa Zai</i>
<i>sent me an email.</i>

249
00:13:42,125 --> 00:13:44,250
<i>That's when I asked him to contact you.</i>

250
00:13:45,375 --> 00:13:46,583
[typing]

251
00:13:46,666 --> 00:13:47,916
CHEN CHIA-JEN

252
00:13:49,708 --> 00:13:51,416
BULGARIAN

253
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:53,500
TRANSLATE

254
00:13:53,583 --> 00:13:54,750
[Chia-jen] Where's the video?

255
00:13:54,833 --> 00:13:56,125
- Huh?
- Where's the video?

256
00:13:56,208 --> 00:13:58,750
[Yo Tzu] The video. You said
the killer sent you a video.

257
00:13:59,583 --> 00:14:01,208
Hang on. Let me find it.

258
00:14:02,291 --> 00:14:03,125
Here.

259
00:14:03,208 --> 00:14:05,041
[tires screech]

260
00:14:05,125 --> 00:14:06,916
- [gear stick rattles]
- [hand brake ratchets]

261
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,083
Let me see.

262
00:14:08,166 --> 00:14:09,750
I've already watched it.

263
00:14:10,625 --> 00:14:13,416
But there's no sound, and you can't tell
where it's filmed at all.

264
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:15,416
[Chia-jen inhales]

265
00:14:18,125 --> 00:14:19,250
Impossible.

266
00:14:19,333 --> 00:14:21,750
[somber music playing]

267
00:14:24,916 --> 00:14:26,750
She keeps looking to the right.

268
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:30,791
[mother] Because you were looking
around at those two.

269
00:14:30,875 --> 00:14:32,958
But you didn't look at this one.

270
00:14:33,583 --> 00:14:35,500
[young Yu-chieh] <i>As if you could tell.</i>

271
00:14:42,416 --> 00:14:43,583
[Chia-jen] What's this?

272
00:14:44,625 --> 00:14:46,500
[Ting-en] A power outlet?

273
00:14:47,958 --> 00:14:49,208
Probably.

274
00:14:49,833 --> 00:14:52,208
- [somber music fades]
- [suspenseful music playing]

275
00:14:52,291 --> 00:14:53,541
Hospital.

276
00:14:53,625 --> 00:14:54,625
Hospital?

277
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:56,500
Hospital.

278
00:14:56,583 --> 00:14:58,333
[music swells]

279
00:15:00,166 --> 00:15:01,875
[device beeps]

280
00:15:08,583 --> 00:15:10,375
[air hissing]

281
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:19,000
VIDEO UPLOAD
UPLOADING FILE

282
00:15:21,791 --> 00:15:23,958
[music continues]

283
00:15:24,625 --> 00:15:25,875
[A-Hua] <i>We met.</i>

284
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:30,708
You treated the shooting victim.
The one with the hemothorax.

285
00:15:31,291 --> 00:15:34,291
Mr. Chen, if you didn't shoot him,
he wouldn't be here, right?

286
00:15:34,375 --> 00:15:36,166
[music subsides, continues]

287
00:15:36,250 --> 00:15:37,125
YU-CHIEH

288
00:15:37,208 --> 00:15:39,166
[messaging app ringback tone playing]

289
00:15:43,708 --> 00:15:45,875
[music swells]

290
00:15:45,958 --> 00:15:47,416
Kuo Ta-fu.

291
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:49,333
[Yo Tzu] That guy?

292
00:15:49,916 --> 00:15:51,500
CALLING LI HSIN-PING

293
00:15:51,583 --> 00:15:56,375
[music continues]

294
00:15:56,458 --> 00:15:58,833
[Hsin-ping's phone ringtone playing]

295
00:15:58,916 --> 00:15:59,916
Hi, Mr. Jen.

296
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:02,375
[Chia-jen on phone] <i>Kuo Ta-fu.</i>
<i>He's now the prime suspect.</i>

297
00:16:02,458 --> 00:16:04,666
<i>Check out his phone</i>
<i>and his present location.</i>

298
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:05,958
Kuo Ta-fu?

299
00:16:06,041 --> 00:16:07,041
Ah…

300
00:16:11,625 --> 00:16:13,416
[music swells]

301
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:14,666
IDENTITY: KILLING SUSPECT
NAME: KUO TA-FU

302
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:15,791
FIFTH FLOOR, NO. 38 LANE, 186 SHUANGHE ST.

303
00:16:15,875 --> 00:16:17,375
PRINT

304
00:16:17,458 --> 00:16:20,333
[music subsides, continues]

305
00:16:20,416 --> 00:16:22,791
[printer whirring]

306
00:16:23,458 --> 00:16:24,458
[Chen-wei clears throat]

307
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,166
Sir.

308
00:16:27,625 --> 00:16:28,833
Now what are you doing?

309
00:16:31,250 --> 00:16:34,708
Mr. Jen wants to investigate Kuo Ta-fu.

310
00:16:34,791 --> 00:16:36,250
Here's a search warrant.

311
00:16:40,125 --> 00:16:41,916
You really don't get it, do you?

312
00:16:42,458 --> 00:16:44,625
You need to take a look at yourself.

313
00:16:46,375 --> 00:16:49,250
- Mr. Jen said that Kuo Ta-fu--
- Mr. Jen, was it?

314
00:16:49,333 --> 00:16:50,333
Which unit are you in?

315
00:16:55,583 --> 00:16:57,458
Mind your own business.

316
00:17:01,541 --> 00:17:02,666
- I'm sorry.
- [Chen-wei knocks]

317
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:04,125
Meeting room. Now.

318
00:17:11,708 --> 00:17:13,958
[Hsin-ping sighs]

319
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:17,166
- Sorry.
- Hey. Don't say sorry.

320
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:20,041
Investigation requires intuition.

321
00:17:20,125 --> 00:17:23,208
<i>If you suspect her,</i>
<i>you must find the evidence.</i>

322
00:17:23,291 --> 00:17:24,333
[Hsin-ping] <i>Yes, sir.</i>

323
00:17:25,833 --> 00:17:28,666
[music continues]

324
00:17:30,875 --> 00:17:31,875
PRINT

325
00:17:31,958 --> 00:17:32,958
[mouse clicks]

326
00:17:34,916 --> 00:17:35,916
[Chang Chieh] Come in.

327
00:17:39,041 --> 00:17:42,583
[Hsin-ping] Sir? Li Hsin-ping.
I have some important information.

328
00:17:44,416 --> 00:17:45,541
It's just you?

329
00:17:46,541 --> 00:17:47,541
[clipboard sets]

330
00:17:50,083 --> 00:17:51,208
What's this?

331
00:17:51,291 --> 00:17:52,458
[Hsin-ping] Sir…

332
00:17:52,541 --> 00:17:56,208
Kuo Ta-fu is now a suspect
in the influencer case.

333
00:17:56,291 --> 00:17:58,875
I'm requesting
your permission to investigate.

334
00:17:58,958 --> 00:18:01,041
Why are you coming to me?

335
00:18:02,416 --> 00:18:03,416
Why not your captain?

336
00:18:09,583 --> 00:18:11,416
Chia-jen said to do this?

337
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:13,833
I know it's awkward.

338
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:19,875
You realize you're bypassing
chain of command.

339
00:18:23,375 --> 00:18:25,625
I know the consequences.

340
00:18:25,708 --> 00:18:27,958
- You do?
- Yes, sir.

341
00:18:28,041 --> 00:18:29,458
And what are they?

342
00:18:33,208 --> 00:18:35,375
I may need to withdraw from my unit.

343
00:18:38,666 --> 00:18:39,666
[Chang Chieh chuckles]

344
00:18:41,125 --> 00:18:43,750
Right now,
that would mean traffic division.

345
00:18:45,041 --> 00:18:46,083
Huh?

346
00:18:48,708 --> 00:18:49,875
[inhales]

347
00:18:49,958 --> 00:18:53,291
I'm prepared for that, sir. If I must.

348
00:18:55,458 --> 00:18:56,458
[Chang Chieh chuckles]

349
00:18:59,875 --> 00:19:01,416
SUPERVISOR: CHANG CHIEH

350
00:19:02,125 --> 00:19:04,166
[phone line ringing]

351
00:19:05,958 --> 00:19:09,166
[music continues]

352
00:19:09,250 --> 00:19:11,416
[ringing continues]

353
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:14,625
CALLING YU-CHIEH

354
00:19:17,041 --> 00:19:19,833
[music fades]

355
00:19:19,916 --> 00:19:21,125
CALLING YU-CHIEH

356
00:19:21,208 --> 00:19:22,208
CALL ENDING

357
00:19:22,291 --> 00:19:23,291
[ringing stops]

358
00:19:25,375 --> 00:19:27,625
Actually, Yu-chieh often talked about you.

359
00:19:28,875 --> 00:19:31,250
She often sounded sad.

360
00:19:32,458 --> 00:19:35,250
But I could tell
she cherished the memories.

361
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:45,166
She was always happy
when you brought her fried rice.

362
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:48,166
[emotional music playing]

363
00:19:48,250 --> 00:19:50,125
She never said that to me.

364
00:19:54,083 --> 00:19:56,666
She said she didn't know how.

365
00:19:58,708 --> 00:20:00,958
I could never really reach her.

366
00:20:03,375 --> 00:20:09,583
She was always…
so involved… in her singing.

367
00:20:14,083 --> 00:20:15,541
All I ever needed to know…

368
00:20:18,625 --> 00:20:22,250
were things like… if she was hungry…

369
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:23,833
DINNER IS BY THE DOOR, REMEMBER TO EAT

370
00:20:23,916 --> 00:20:25,250
…or if she was happy…

371
00:20:25,333 --> 00:20:26,625
YU-CHIEH - SHARE

372
00:20:26,708 --> 00:20:28,500
…or if someone bullied her.

373
00:20:33,541 --> 00:20:34,541
[taps phone]

374
00:20:35,375 --> 00:20:37,833
[phone line ringing]

375
00:20:40,625 --> 00:20:43,333
CALLING YU-CHIEH

376
00:20:43,416 --> 00:20:45,458
- [emotional music stops]
- [unsettling music playing]

377
00:20:45,541 --> 00:20:47,458
[phone buzzing]

378
00:20:47,541 --> 00:20:48,875
DAD

379
00:21:04,083 --> 00:21:05,500
[Ta-fu sighs]

380
00:21:06,625 --> 00:21:08,041
Your dad's calling.

381
00:21:08,666 --> 00:21:10,416
Should I pass a message?

382
00:21:16,208 --> 00:21:17,416
[Yu-chieh] "Save me."

383
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:21,416
Save? [chuckles]

384
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:26,291
I've been using your phone to text him
for a week, and he never noticed.

385
00:21:26,916 --> 00:21:29,458
You think he loves you enough
to come save you?

386
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:34,333
Do you have a daughter?

387
00:21:39,833 --> 00:21:42,083
Then you wouldn't understand.

388
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:46,916
[phone drops]

389
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:49,375
- [Ta-fu] Fuck!
- [porcelain shatters]

390
00:21:49,458 --> 00:21:50,541
[music swells]

391
00:21:50,625 --> 00:21:51,791
[Yu-chieh yelps]

392
00:21:51,875 --> 00:21:53,875
[Ta-fu] You guys
fucking killed my daughter!

393
00:21:53,958 --> 00:21:55,291
[Yu-chieh] Get off me!

394
00:21:56,083 --> 00:21:58,708
- [kick lands]
- [Ta-fu grunts, breathing heavily]

395
00:22:01,625 --> 00:22:02,708
[tape rips]

396
00:22:04,583 --> 00:22:06,500
[Yu-chieh speaks indistinctly, muffled]

397
00:22:07,083 --> 00:22:08,500
[grunts, muffled]

398
00:22:10,208 --> 00:22:13,083
[music continues]

399
00:22:13,166 --> 00:22:14,166
[door closes]

400
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:19,208
[Yu-chieh grunting, muffled]

401
00:22:21,791 --> 00:22:23,458
[crying]

402
00:22:24,041 --> 00:22:28,875
Sir? Kuo Ta-fu's wife died a year ago.
Result of a miscarriage.

403
00:22:28,958 --> 00:22:31,375
<i>Her heart stopped.</i>
<i>Both mother and daughter died.</i>

404
00:22:31,458 --> 00:22:33,791
- [Chia-jen] They both died.
<i>- Yes. Before they reached the hospital.</i>

405
00:22:34,375 --> 00:22:36,250
When was this? A year ago?

406
00:22:36,875 --> 00:22:39,208
[Hsin-ping] <i>3:23 a.m. on the 19th.</i>

407
00:22:39,291 --> 00:22:40,291
[music swells]

408
00:22:40,375 --> 00:22:41,375
[Ting-en] Oh. Sorry.

409
00:22:41,458 --> 00:22:43,833
- [scooter honking]
- [fireworks popping]

410
00:22:43,916 --> 00:22:46,000
- [tires screech]
- [loud crash]

411
00:22:48,041 --> 00:22:51,666
[harrowing music playing]

412
00:22:51,750 --> 00:22:52,583
[Ting-en] Hey.

413
00:22:54,416 --> 00:22:55,708
What's wrong?

414
00:22:59,791 --> 00:23:03,000
[music ends]

415
00:23:03,083 --> 00:23:08,416
[unsettling music playing]

416
00:23:18,833 --> 00:23:19,875
[Yu-chieh grunts]

417
00:23:21,583 --> 00:23:23,250
- [grunting]
- [kicks landing]

418
00:23:25,833 --> 00:23:27,166
[porcelain clinking]

419
00:23:29,375 --> 00:23:32,250
[Yu-chieh breathing deeply]

420
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:39,125
[door bangs]

421
00:23:39,625 --> 00:23:41,166
[footsteps running, receding]

422
00:23:41,250 --> 00:23:44,750
[low voice] I last have Kuo Ta-fu
at the West Hospital Building.

423
00:23:44,833 --> 00:23:48,583
It's abandoned, but sometimes it's used
as a temporary doctor's dormitory.

424
00:23:48,666 --> 00:23:49,666
Got it.

425
00:23:54,291 --> 00:23:57,666
WEST HOSPITAL BUILDING

426
00:24:03,916 --> 00:24:05,208
[music continues]

427
00:24:05,291 --> 00:24:06,791
WEST BUILDING - EAST BUILDING

428
00:24:14,125 --> 00:24:15,125
Yu-chieh!

429
00:24:17,291 --> 00:24:18,458
[in distance] Yu-chieh!

430
00:24:18,541 --> 00:24:21,166
[Yu-chieh speaks indistinctly, muffled]

431
00:24:23,583 --> 00:24:25,791
[music swelling]

432
00:24:25,875 --> 00:24:26,875
[handgun clicks]

433
00:24:36,958 --> 00:24:38,625
[music subsides, continues]

434
00:24:51,291 --> 00:24:52,333
[Yu-chieh yells, muffled]

435
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:59,000
[yells, muffled]

436
00:25:15,916 --> 00:25:19,125
[suspenseful music playing]

437
00:25:30,208 --> 00:25:31,291
[porcelain clinks]

438
00:25:32,708 --> 00:25:34,708
[music swells, continues]

439
00:25:35,291 --> 00:25:37,041
- [basket rattles]
- [feet shuffle]

440
00:25:39,500 --> 00:25:40,500
[Yu-chieh] Dad!

441
00:25:40,583 --> 00:25:42,041
[Yu-chieh's feet shuffle in distance]

442
00:25:44,833 --> 00:25:49,375
[music continues, swelling]

443
00:25:49,458 --> 00:25:50,458
[Yu-chieh yelps]

444
00:25:50,541 --> 00:25:53,166
[Ta-fu breathing heavily]

445
00:25:53,250 --> 00:25:54,291
[Chia-jen] Yu-chieh!

446
00:25:54,875 --> 00:25:57,625
[music subsides]

447
00:25:57,708 --> 00:25:59,083
[door opens]

448
00:26:08,166 --> 00:26:09,375
[Ta-fu grunts]

449
00:26:09,916 --> 00:26:15,625
[breathing heavily]

450
00:26:24,333 --> 00:26:25,333
[car door closes]

451
00:26:25,416 --> 00:26:27,833
- [ignition lock clicks]
- [engine starts]

452
00:26:33,375 --> 00:26:34,791
[gear stick rattles]

453
00:26:39,083 --> 00:26:41,083
[music fades]

454
00:26:48,083 --> 00:26:50,000
Hey. Don't come in. It stinks.

455
00:26:50,083 --> 00:26:51,458
[melancholy music playing]

456
00:26:51,541 --> 00:26:53,333
You're painting again?

457
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:56,291
[Ta-fu] I didn't know
we were having a daughter back then.

458
00:26:56,375 --> 00:27:00,416
I told you. Just paint it white.
White goes with everything.

459
00:27:00,500 --> 00:27:02,250
Yeah, but white?

460
00:27:02,333 --> 00:27:04,500
Looks like a hospital. It's boring.

461
00:27:05,375 --> 00:27:07,333
What if our daughter likes blue?

462
00:27:07,416 --> 00:27:08,916
Then I'll change it back for her.

463
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:11,541
[wife chuckles] You have
too much free time.

464
00:27:11,625 --> 00:27:13,083
Get back to work.

465
00:27:13,166 --> 00:27:14,000
[Ta-fu] Hey.

466
00:27:14,083 --> 00:27:17,833
I think this is the perfect opportunity
to spend time with Ni-ni.

467
00:27:19,666 --> 00:27:22,250
Babe. I don't like "Ni-ni."

468
00:27:23,416 --> 00:27:24,416
It's cute.

469
00:27:24,500 --> 00:27:26,291
But what would the fortune teller say?

470
00:27:27,416 --> 00:27:28,250
Right.

471
00:27:28,958 --> 00:27:33,333
- Then, next week, we'll ask him.
- No. Today.

472
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:35,458
The paint's not even dry yet.

473
00:27:35,541 --> 00:27:40,583
Well, Ni-ni said
she wants to go out today.

474
00:27:44,458 --> 00:27:46,208
- Mmm?
- [chuckles] Okay.

475
00:27:46,291 --> 00:27:48,125
[both chuckle]

476
00:27:48,208 --> 00:27:50,208
[wife] Kuo Mei-mei.

477
00:27:51,208 --> 00:27:52,750
Kuo Lian-li.

478
00:27:53,708 --> 00:27:55,791
Kuo Ching-ching.

479
00:27:56,916 --> 00:27:58,916
Kuo Fen-jong.

480
00:27:59,666 --> 00:28:01,083
Kuo Pi-chien.

481
00:28:01,625 --> 00:28:03,333
- Kuo…
- Kuo Hsueh-fu?

482
00:28:03,416 --> 00:28:05,833
Ugh. You know I don't like that name.

483
00:28:05,916 --> 00:28:07,000
All right.

484
00:28:09,208 --> 00:28:12,541
Why can't we get her fortune read
before she's born?

485
00:28:12,625 --> 00:28:15,375
What can he read?
There's no birth details.

486
00:28:15,458 --> 00:28:18,333
So? But she's due soon.

487
00:28:19,958 --> 00:28:21,000
[tapping phone]

488
00:28:23,125 --> 00:28:24,125
[gasps]

489
00:28:25,041 --> 00:28:28,458
- [chuckles] Hey. Who bought this?
- [chuckles]

490
00:28:30,083 --> 00:28:32,500
You keep buying her shoes!

491
00:28:33,500 --> 00:28:38,500
Well, dear. A girl
can never have enough shoes.

492
00:28:41,458 --> 00:28:42,458
[chuckles]

493
00:28:42,541 --> 00:28:45,125
- Ah. I've trained you well.
- I learned from the best.

494
00:28:45,208 --> 00:28:47,458
- [influencers cheering, chattering]
- [Ta-fu] What the hell?

495
00:28:47,541 --> 00:28:50,125
- [fireworks popping]
- [scooter honking]

496
00:28:50,208 --> 00:28:51,416
What are they doing?

497
00:28:51,500 --> 00:28:53,416
- [melancholy music fades]
- [uneasy music playing]

498
00:28:53,500 --> 00:28:56,541
[influencers cheering, chattering]

499
00:28:57,125 --> 00:28:58,125
[wife groans]

500
00:29:00,666 --> 00:29:03,291
- [Ta-fu] Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

501
00:29:03,375 --> 00:29:05,000
I'm fine. I'll be fine.

502
00:29:06,333 --> 00:29:09,000
Hey, just let them go. Don't get involved.

503
00:29:09,083 --> 00:29:11,416
[Ta-fu] No. They're way out of line.
This is ridiculous.

504
00:29:14,083 --> 00:29:16,291
